  "description": "Our proteomics dataset comes from The PRoteomics IDEntifications (PRIDE) database, the world\u2019s largest data repository of mass spectrometry-based proteomics data. Specifically, we used 633 human proteomics project experiments with a total of 32,546 runs and reanalyzed them using ionbot with an FDR threshold of 0.01 [16], resulting in a total of 154,885,151 peptide spectrum matches for 18,846 proteins. Here is the full list of projects, runs, and general statistics.",
